@LAR First of all, welcome! I think you'll find this community supportive, although you might aim to post earlier in the day for a better range of responses. As for using autocheck: It's *not* a bad thing. I believe Deb has told us that she solves with autocheck on; solving is part of her job, and she's not concerned with streaks. She (and others) have repeatedly told us it's a game, it's supposed to be fun, and it's YOUR puzzle. You make up the rules you want to solve by, and then try to stick to them. 

Barry's not wrong; as you gain experience and confidence you will probably want to turn off autocheck at least for your first few passes, or for early-week puzzles--again, you make your rules and you do you. If you're feeling stumped you can always come here for hints, or to ask for help. 

again, welcome.

